                        <div id="menu1" class="tab-pane fade">
                            <div class="panel panel-default text-left">
                                <div class=panel-heading>
                                    <h3>Dormitory</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="panel-body">

                                    <p>
                                        The campus consists of 5 high-rise buildings and 2 level-4 ranks with 320 rooms (of which 150 rooms are equipped with cable TV), with closed works, full electricity and water supply for students, school students.

                                        The total number of accommodation is 2800, of which 200 students, 2200 students, graduate students, students and foreign students: 400. The subjects are in dormitories from 01 to 06 according to the regime
                                    </p>
                                    <p>Students admitted to the dorm must adhere to the general regulations of the dormitory.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div id="menu2" class="tab-pane fade">
                            <div class="panel panel-default text-left">
                                <div class="panel-heading">
                                    <h3> Library</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>
                                        The University Library Information Center is located in a four-storey building with an area of ??approximately 5,000 square meters and nearly 1,000 seats with a full range of specialized equipment and furniture suitable for library activities.
                                    </p>

                                    <p>The center has 33 staff (including 07 masters, 26 bachelors) and 8 security and hygiene staff.</p>

                                    <p>The center has 04 main functional rooms: Business Division, Reading Room, Loan Room and Informatics Division.</p>

                                    <p>Business Unit: Performs research, collects, selects, replaces, processes and develops traditional and modern search systems. In addition, this is a place to carry out necessary procedures for readers at the beginning of the course such as: Building a reader's profile of the Center, the procedures for receiving and payment of book money of students upon enrollment and before Upon graduation, handle violations of the rules of reading and payment to the school for readers. The Office is located in rooms 102, 103, 104 - 1st floor of the Center.</p>

                                    <p>Reading Room: A place to organize, store and preserve documents and provide you with readings needed to read on-the-spot with reading rooms (warehouse, warehouse - rooms 301, 302 - 3rd floor). reading rooms, magazines, theses and dissertations (storehouse 401, 4th floor) and newspapers and magazines (open storage - room 203 - floor 2) of the Center.</p>

                                    <p>Borrowing: is a place to organize, store and preserve documents and serve for borrowers to read materials at home within the prescribed time with 2 rooms: borrowing room (room 101 - floor 1) and borrowing room (room 201 - floor 2) of the Center. Students are provided with a schedule of assignments for each department on specific days of the week and the loan term is semester. Reference books are borrowed weekly.</p>

                                    <p>
                                        Computer Science Department: Serving readers, Internet users and multimedia system with electronic resources, located in rooms 402, 403, 404, 405 - 4th floor of the Center.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Document:

                                        Up to the end of the second quarter of 2011, the total documented capital of the Center as follows:
                                    </p>
                                    <p>Books: 74,200 titles 347,000 books.</p>
                                    <p>Newspaper: 40 names (Saved from 1980 to present).</p>
                                    <p>Magazine: 935 names = 46,000 copies.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        Theses and dissertations: 10,300 names = 13,000 copies.
                                        Research topic: 2,500 names = 4,500 books.
                                        Proceeding: 319 names = 372 copies.
                                        All kinds of documents such as books, newspapers, magazines, theses, dissertations, scientific studies, etc., of the following languages: English, German, Russian, Chinese ...

                                        Electronic documents include:

                                        Catssette tape: 157 tapes.
                                        Video tape: 87 tapes.
                                        CD-ROM: 1,259 discs.
                                        Databases: English learning software, American Journal of Educational Sciences, Vietnamese journals, Vietnamese and Vietnamese e-Government research databases, online e-journals of the American Institute of Physics (IOP), Royal Society of Chemistry (RSC).

                                        In addition, the Center has built a bibliographic database of 74,735 records for books, theses, dissertations, magazine essays.

                                        Software used in the Center is dedicated software Libol 5.5 of Tinhvan Information Technology Company with 7 modules used as: Add, Catalog, OPAC, Circulation, Readers, Publications and System Management. Read and manage the loan and return documents on the computer, ensure fast, accurate.
                                    </p>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
