                                    <h3>Clinics</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p>Capmpus Health Station was built right after the campus was established, precursor is only a medical team with the task of health care for staff, lecturers and students of the school.</p>

                                    <p>
                                        At present, the Health Station has 11 staff, including; 3 doctors, 2 doctors, 6 nurses.

                                        With the staff of the above staff, the medical station has carried out a series of tasks assigned by the school, including health care for staffs and students, students in the whole school.

                                    <p>Students entering school:</p>

                                    - Must have health examination as prescribed by the Ministry of Education and Training.


                                    - Should be insured to get compensation when the risk of accident or sickness surgery, hospitalization.

                                    <p>During school:</p>

                                    <p>
                                        - Students are entitled to medical examination and treatment in accordance with the Law on Health Insurance with the following procedures:
                                    </p>
                                    <p>+ Patients who come to the clinic for medical examination and presentation of health insurance card to register for medical treatment at health agency (code 01 - 148) and photo ID (student card, student ID card or ID card people).</p>
                                    <p>
                                        + The medical staff of the station shall conduct the medical examination and diagnosis of the disease: if the patient is capable of treating the station, the patient is given an outpatient treatment by the doctor; In cases beyond the treatment capacity of the station, the patient is transferred to the upper level of treatment (line where the station has the right to transfer).
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        - When you need to leave school to treat your illness, you must go to the school health station for confirmation of the reason for a valid stay. If you need medical examination, you must show the medical certificate. there.

                                        Students before graduation: Must have medical examination at the school's Health Station according to the informed schedule.

                                        The medical station always sends emergency medical personnel 24 hours a day to provide emergency assistance when there are emergency patients.
                                    </p>
